'''Soumana Makadji''' (born 1954 in [[Banamba]], [[Mali]]) was Minister of Health and Public Hygiene in the [[Council of Ministers of Mali]] from 17 April 2012 to September 2013, replacing Oumar Ibrahim Touré.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.primature.gov.ml/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=8421&Itemid=100013|title= Le Gouvernement du mardi 24 avril 2012|date= 2012-04-26|accessdate= 2012-07-02|work= Primature|publisher= [[Government of Mali]]|language= French|deadurl= yes|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20120514143954/http://www.primature.gov.ml/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=8421&Itemid=100013|archivedate= 2012-05-14|df= }}</ref> After obtaining his baccalauréat in 1973 at the Technical High School of Bamako, he studied in [[University of Franche-Comté]] ([[Besançon]] campus) and obtained a diploma in Accountancy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://malijet.com/people-mali/qui-est-qui-au-mali/qui-est-qui-en-politique/65011-soumana-makadji.html|publisher=Malijet.net|date=3 February 2013|language=French|title=Soumana Makadji}}</ref>

