'''Titan Pharmaceuticals, Inc.''' is a biopharmaceutical company based in [[San Francisco, CA]] developing proprietary therapeutics primarily for the treatment of central nervous system ("CNS") disorders. In September of 2018, Titan Pharmaceuticals underwent an [[Initial Public Offering|IPO]] wherein it raised $9.5 million in gross proceeds.<ref>https://www.streetinsider.com/Equity+Offerings/Titan+Pharma+%28TTNP%29+Prices+%249.5M+Public+Offering/14630497.html</ref> In the same month, it also posted approximately $1.7 million in revenue, in large part drawn from its licensing for its European intellectual property rights for Probuphine to the Italian pharmaceutical company Molteni - a leading European opioid manufacturer and also a subsidiary of the German Pharmaceutical juggernaut [[Merck Group]].<ref>https://www.titanpharm.com/news/press-releases/detail/204/titan-pharmaceuticals-reports-third-quarter-2018-financial</ref><ref>https://www.thepharmaletter.com/article/germany-s-merck-kgaa-taking-over-molteni-pharma-of-italy</ref>
Titan's principal asset is [[Probuphine]],<ref name=titprob/><ref name=10k>http://ir.titanpharm.com/annual-reports#document-21870-0001144204-17-014986</ref> a slow-release implant formulation of buprenorphine<ref name=bs13/> for the treatment of [[opioid addiction]] or chronic pain. FDA Approval was granted on 26 May 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.fda.gov/NewsEvents/Newsroom/PressAnnouncements/ucm503719.htm|title=Press Announcements - FDA approves first buprenorphine implant for treatment of opioid dependence|website=www.fda.gov|language=en|access-date=26 May 2016}}</ref> It was licensed to [[Braeburn Pharmaceuticals]] for marketing and commercialization.<ref name=10k/>
== 2018 ==
As of its November 14th [[earnings call]], Titan Pharmaceuticals is on track to commercialize its opioid addiction solution at a valuation between $75 and $100 million dollars.<ref>https://www.webcaster4.com/Webcast/Page/1655/28313</ref>
